{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Proteins in this family are phosphodiesterases responsible for trimming the poly (U) tract of the last nucleotides in the pre-U6 snRNA molecule, leading to the formation of mature U6 snRNA [[cite:PUB00064790], [cite:PUB00100252]].</p>\n\n<p>In Saccharomyces cerevisiae, Usb1 is an essential protein that localises to the nucleus and mitochondria [[cite:PUB00016470]]. Usb1 overexpression can compensate for specific respiratory defects of an oxa1 yeast mutant [[cite:PUB00066979]].</p>\n\n<p>In humans, Usb1 is localised to the nucleus and is involved in the 2',3'-cyclic phosphate formation at the 3' end of U6 snRNA [[cite:PUB00064790]]. The human protein has been shown to degrade both oligo(U) and oligo(A) tails at the 3' end of U6 snRNA [[cite:PUB00065818]]. Its crystal structure has been solved and shows a globular α-β-type architecture [[cite:PUB00065818]]. Mutation in Usb1 is linked to poikiloderma with neutropenia (PN), a genodermatosis characterised by poikiloderma, pachyonychia and chronic neutropenia [[cite:PUB00066977], [cite:PUB00066978]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4h7w", "name" "Crystal Structure of Human C16orf57"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF09749" "Uncharacterised conserved protein"}, "hamap" {"MF_03040" "U6 snRNA phosphodiesterase [USB1]"}, "panther" {"PTHR13522" "U6 SNRNA PHOSPHODIESTERASE 1"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "U6 snRNA phosphodiesterase 1", "short" "Usb1"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 8, "domain_architectures" 61, "proteomes" 2320, "taxa" 7913, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 4102, "sets" 0, "proteins" 4056, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2652}, "pathways" 5}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of en